Defendant in custody on WRIT.
On count 5, possess cocaine with intent to deliver, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on Milwaukee County case no: 08 CF 5925.
On count 1, deliver cocaine, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five (5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with count 5.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) No possession of any weapons;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Complete sobriety and abstinence from illegal drug use;
4) No possession of alcohol, drugs or drug paraphernalia;
5) Cognitive behavior programming;
6) Work toward completion of GED or HSED;
7) Enrollment in vocational training and literary services;
8) Pay court costs;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
11) pay $500.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
